sec.p:
The chi-square test revealed a notable increase in the prevalence of POSA within the mild OSA population compared to NPOSA. Conversely, patients diagnosed with severe OSA exhibited a higher prevalence of NPOSA compared to POSA. Furthermore, individuals with non-allergic rhinitis and allergic rhinitis illustrated a higher prevalence of POSA in comparison to NPOSA. Lastly, in patients with obesity, the prevalence of POSA was higher than that of NPOSA, although this comparison was not statistically significant (Table 2). The proportion of patients with a history of bronchial asthma did not significantly differ between the NPOSA and POSA groups (Table S3).Table 2
